 *
 * @remarks
 *
 * Represents a cubemap texture resource in the material node graph. A cubemap consists of 6 square textures representing the faces of a cube, sampled using a 3D direction vector.
 *
 * Used for: - Environment maps (skyboxes) - Reflections (environment reflections on shiny surfaces) - Image-based lighting (IBL) - Irradiance maps for ambient lighting - Prefiltered environment maps for specular reflections
 *
 * Cubemap faces (standard ordering): - +X (right), -X (left) - +Y (top), -Y (bottom) - +Z (front), -Z (back)
